pr_review_comment_body:
yes and actually I have also missed to add another argument in `check_artifact` function.

 But what I am now finding contradictory is that if we pass single addon  [this](https://github.com/xbmc/addon-check/blob/master/kodi_addon_checker/__main__.py#L41) will directly call the start function. But we are getting [`repo_addons`](https://github.com/xbmc/addon-check/pull/63/files#diff-87cbf8a463aa7f67c8382bdac08ec809R15) from `check_repo` function. So I'll have to do this within the start function but if I do that then we'll have the same issue of having multiple requests for same repo i.e caching addon.xml.

@Razzeee Am I on the right track or have I missed something here ?

There's quite a bit of duplication above. At least the `elif` could be changed to `if` and two lines above it removed, but perhaps the code could be simplified to this:

```python
    def _get_screenshot_paths(self, filename):
        if not filename:
            filename = 'selenium-screenshot-{index}.png'
        else:
            filename = filename.replace('/', os.sep)
        filename = filename.format(index=self._get_screenshot_index(filename))
```

This should be a single translatable string with placeholders:
```
{{ _('Discussion started on {created} with {nb} messages', {
    created: discussion.created|dt,
    nb: response.length
}) }}
```
